content.description: Climb towards the overhang, and go left of it and through the drill holes.
content.location: It is on the left side of the ledge.

content.description: This climb links the lower three drill holes with the upper two. Well named. One variation of Drills Holes eliminates the large "K-te;" ledge 12 feet up, as well as the "Ronco" and "Acme" holds. Another variation uses the right two lower drill holes as the start.
content.location: This is where the three drills holes meet the large belay/ hangout ledge.

content.description: Pass the overhang on the right and continue up to the right of the next overhang.
content.location: Under the overhang to the right of the three drill holes.

content.description:
This is a small wall just to the right of C Face.  In fact, it is really a continuation of that face.  Fingers, the right-most route of C Face, is on the left margin of this face.  It continues with E Face on its left. There was a fair bit of loose rock on this face.  There are apparently bolt anchors at the top of the wall. The drill holes on this face make for some unusual climbing.  The descent is on the right. 

  L->R: 

  A. Fingers, 7, 1p, TR.   B. Meat Cleaver, 4, 1p, TR.   CB. Upshot, 6, 1p, TR.   D1. Drill Holes, 6 PG-13, TR.   D2. Eliminates of big holds/ledge   D3. Eliminate with only right holes   D. Extensor, 8, 1p, TR.   ED. Condenser, 6, 1p, TR.   E. Condenser Direct, 6, 1p, TR.
